    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available now is an exceptional 2002 BMW M3 (E46) in collector-grade condition. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54B32 3.2L straight-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a forged steel crankshaft. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M-Differential lock. This unit has undergone rigorous preventative maintenance, including a comprehensive dual-VANOS overhaul and professional rear subframe reinforcement to address known chassis fatigue points. The suspension retains its original kinematics with refreshed bushings, ensuring the McPherson strut front and multi-link rear setups provide peak lateral grip. With a documented service history, no pixel loss on the instrument cluster, and a leak-free undercarriage, this M3 represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated M-division performance.",
